<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}-{8}{y}={8}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}+{y}=-{14}</m></p>
<p><input type="text" style="width:10.6ch" name="qn0" id="qn0" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1" class="text"/></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({2},-{2}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+-{8}{y}={8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}={8}-{\left(-{8}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{{8}-{\left(-{8}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{4}}}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{\left(\frac{{{8}-{\left(-{8}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{4}}}}\right)}+{1}{y}=-{14}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{6}}{{-{{4}}}}\cdot{\left({8}\right)}--\frac{{6}}{{-{{4}}}}{\left(-{8}\right)}{y}+{1}{y}=-{14}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{12}-{\left({12}\right)}{y}+{1}{y}=-{14}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{12}{y}+{\left({1}\right)}{y}=-{14}-{12}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{12}{y}+{\left({1}\right)}{y}=-{26}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left({12}+{\left({1}\right)}\right)}{y}=-{26}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{13}{y}=-{26}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{26}}{{13}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{2}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+-{8}{\left(-{2}\right)}={8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+{\left({16}\right)}={8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}={8}-{\left({16}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}=-{8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{8}}{{-{{4}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={2}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({2},-{2}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
